    "text": "Applying the No-Signaling Null-Boundary predictor from the Null-Boundary Response framework to the Italian incentive-quality dataset (D6.10) will show that any statistically significant effect of incentives on quality metrics is entirely due to leakage across administrative boundaries, and when correcting via null-boundary blocking, the effect vanishes (p > 0.5 for all incentive level contrasts).",
